article.description: — Treysen Eaglestaff's 23 points helped North Dakota defeat New Orleans 71-69 in overtime on Saturday at the Central Arkansas Classic.
article.headline: Eaglestaff's 23 help North Dakota down New Orleans 71-69 in OT at Central Arkansas Classic
article.linkText: Eaglestaff's 23 help North Dakota down New Orleans 71-69 in OT at Central Arkansas Classic
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- — Treysen Eaglestaff's 23 points helped North Dakota defeat New Orleans 71-69 in overtime on Saturday at the Central Arkansas Classic. Eaglestaff added six rebounds and five assists for the Fightin' Hawks (4-1). Amar Kuljuhovic added 15 points while going 4 of 4 and 7 of 11 from the free-throw line, and they also had 10 rebounds and three steals. Elijah Brooks had 12 points and finished 6 of 8 from the floor. Jordan Johnson led the way for the Privateers (2-3) with 18 points. Khaleb Wilson-Rouse added 16 points and four steals for New Orleans. Carlos Hart also put up 12 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
